---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const updated = 'June 1, 2026';
const title = `Cookie Policy | ${SITE.name}`;
const description = `How ${SITE.name} uses cookies and local storage: essential only by default, optional analytics with your consent, and never to store the data you enter.`;
---

<LegalLayout title={title} description={description} heading="Cookie Policy" updated={updated}>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains how {SITE.name} uses cookies and similar technologies
    (such as browser local storage) when you visit our website. It should be read
    alongside our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They
    help sites remember your actions and preferences. "Local storage" is a similar
    technology that lets a site save small pieces of data in your browser. We use both
    sparingly.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use them</h2>
  <p>We keep our use of these technologies to a minimum, in two categories:</p>

  <h3>Essential (always on)</h3>
  <p>
    These are necessary for the site to function and remember your basic choices. They
    do not track you across other sites. For example, we store your cookie-consent
    decision in local storage (under a key such as <code>hls-consent</code>) so we don't
    ask you again on every visit.
  </p>

  <h3>Analytics (optional, consent-based)</h3>
  <p>
    With your consent, we may use privacy-respecting analytics to understand which tools
    are useful and how to improve the site. These are loaded <strong>only</strong> after
    you select "Accept all" in our cookie banner. If you choose "Reject non-essential",
    no analytics cookies are set.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies we do not use</h2>
  <p>
    We do not use advertising cookies to build marketing profiles of you, and we do not
    sell your data. Crucially, <strong>we never use cookies to store the health
    information you enter into our calculators</strong> — those values are processed in
    your browser and discarded.
  </p>

  <h2>Managing your choices</h2>
  <p>You are in control of cookies in two ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Our cookie banner:</strong> Choose "Accept all" or "Reject non-essential"
      when you first visit. To change your decision later, clear this site's data in your
      browser and the banner will reappear.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Your browser settings:</strong> Most browsers let you block or delete
      cookies and local storage. Note that blocking essential storage may mean the consent
      banner reappears on each visit.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-party cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Any optional analytics provider we use may set its own cookies when enabled with your
    consent. These providers are selected for their respect for user privacy and are not
    permitted to use the data for their own advertising.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Cookie Policy as our practices or the law evolve. The "Last
    updated" date above reflects the latest revision.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about our use of cookies, please
    <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
